 "target_response": {
  "text": "Training load is a single-session score of cardiovascular stress, built from how hard your heart worked and for how long, on a scale where your tracker caps out at 21. Yesterday's 17.5 came from a 90-minute strength session where you averaged 135 bpm and peaked at 189 bpm; long duration plus sustained elevated heart rate is exactly what pushes the number toward the top of the scale. For calibration, your 7-day strain average is 11.2, so this was a well-above-average day for you, which makes it a session your body needs real recovery from. It handled it: this morning's recovery is 73% with HRV at 60 ms, above your 30-day average of 56.8. One caveat is that load leans on heart rate, which undercounts pure strength stress like heavy low-rep work, so treat it as a floor for lifting days rather than the whole truth.",
